同样因为被积函数为奇函数，易算出 $\langle \hat{x} \rangle_{\psi} = 0$

$$
\left\langle \hat{x}^{2} \right\rangle_{\psi} = \frac{2}{L} \int_{0}^{\infty} \mathrm{e}^{-2 x / L} x^{2} \mathrm{~d} x = \frac{L^{2}}{2}
$$

故有 $\Delta_{\psi} \hat{x} = \frac{L}{\sqrt{2}}$。下面求 $\Delta_{\psi} \hat{p}$.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{因为 } \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} = \left[\frac{1}{L} - \frac{2}{L} \theta(x)\right] \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L}, \text{ 其中 } \\
\theta(x)= 
\begin{cases}
1, & x>0, \\
0, & x<0 
\end{cases}
\end{aligned}
$$

为阶梯函数，故有

$$
\frac{\partial^{2}}{\partial x^{2}} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} = -\frac{2}{L} \delta(x) \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} + \frac{1}{L^{2}} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L}
$$

因此

$$
\begin{aligned}
\langle \hat{p} \rangle & = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{\sqrt{L}} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \left[-\mathrm{i} \hbar \frac{\partial}{\partial x}\right] \frac{1}{\sqrt{L}} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \mathrm{~d} x \\
& = -\mathrm{i} \hbar \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{L} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \left[\frac{1}{L} - \frac{2}{L} \theta(x)\right] \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \mathrm{~d} x = 0, \\
\left\langle \hat{p}^{2} \right\rangle & = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{L} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \left(-\hbar^{2} \frac{\partial^{2}}{\partial x^{2}}\right) \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \mathrm{~d} x \\
& = -\hbar^{2} \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{L} \left[\frac{2}{L} \delta(x) - \frac{1}{L^{2}}\right] \mathrm{e}^{-2|x| / L} \mathrm{~d} x \\
& = \frac{2 \hbar^{2}}{L} |\psi(0)|^{2} - \frac{\hbar^{2}}{L^{2}} = \frac{\hbar^{2}}{L^{2}}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\Delta_{\psi} \hat{p}=\frac{\hbar}{L}
$$

也可以转到动量空间求解

$$
\begin{aligned}
\psi(p) & = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi \hbar L}} \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \mathrm{e}^{-|x| / L} \mathrm{e}^{-\mathrm{i} p x / \hbar} \mathrm{d} x = \frac{2}{\sqrt{2 \pi \hbar L}} \int_{0}^{\infty} \mathrm{e}^{-x / L} \cos \left(\frac{p}{\hbar} x \right) \mathrm{d} x \\
& = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi \hbar L}} \cdot \frac{2 / L}{p^{2} / \hbar^{2} + 1 / L^{2}}, \\
\left\langle \hat{p}^{2} \right\rangle_{\psi} & = \frac{1}{2 \pi \hbar L} \int_{0}^{\infty} \left(\frac{2 / L}{p^{2} / \hbar^{2} + 1 / L^{2}}\right)^{2} p^{2} \mathrm{~d} p = \frac{\hbar^{2}}{L^{2}}
\end{aligned}
$$

上面利用了积分公式

$$
\int \frac{\mathrm{d} x}{\left(a^{2} + x^{2}\right)^{n}} = 
\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{a} \arctan \frac{x}{a}, & n = 1 \\
\frac{x}{2(n-1) a^{2}\left(a^{2} + x^{2}\right)^{n-1}} + \frac{2n-3}{2(n-1) a^{2}} \int \frac{\mathrm{~d} x}{\left(a^{2} + x^{2}\right)^{n-1}}, & n > 1
\end{cases}
$$

由上面计算可知 $\left(\Delta_{\psi} \hat{x}\right)\left(\Delta_{\psi} \hat{p}\right) = \frac{\hbar}{\sqrt{2}} > \frac{\hbar}{2}$。

